{{Infobox Figure Skating Competition | title= 1987 Prize of Moscow News | imagesize= | caption= | comptype= | startdate= November 11 | enddate= 15 | skatingseason= 1987-88 | location= [[Moscow]] | host= | venue= | prizemoney= | championmen= {{flagathlete|[[Alexandre Fadeev]]|URS}} | championladies= {{flagathlete| [[Cindy Bortz]]|USA}} | championpairs= {{flagathlete|[[Ekaterina Gordeeva]] / [[Sergei Grinkov]]|URS}} | championdance= {{flagathlete|[[Marina Klimova]] / [[Sergei Ponomarenko]]|URS}} | previouscomp= [[1986 Prize of Moscow News]] | nextcomp= [[1988 Prize of Moscow News]] | previousgp= | nextgp= }}
The '''1987 [[Prize of Moscow News]]''' was the 22nd edition of an international figure skating competition organized in [[Moscow]], [[Soviet Union]]. It was held November 11–15, 1987. Medals were awarded in the disciplines of [[single skating|men's singles, ladies' singles]], [[pair skating]] and [[ice dancing]]. The men's title went to World champion [[Alexandre Fadeev]], winning the Prize of Moscow News for the fourth time. [[Cindy Bortz]], moving up to the senior level after winning the world junior title, won the ladies' category. [[Ekaterina Gordeeva]] / [[Sergei Grinkov]], who would win the Olympic gold medal later in the season, took the pairs' title ahead of 1984 Olympic champions [[Elena Valova]] / [[Oleg Vasiliev (figure skater)|Oleg Vasiliev]]. The ice dancing title was won by [[Marina Klimova]] / [[Sergei Ponomarenko]], who would end their season with an Olympic silver medal.
