{{Year nav|-519}} {{BC year in topic|519}}
The year '''519 BC''' was a year of the [[Roman calendar|pre-Julian Roman calendar]]. In the [[Roman Empire]], it was known as '''year 235 '' [[Ab urbe condita]]'''''. The denomination 519 BC for this year has been used since the early medieval period, when the [[Anno Domini]] [[calendar era]] became the prevalent method in Europe for naming years.
== Events ==
=== By place === ==== China ==== *[[King Jing of Zhou (Gai)|Zhou Jing Wang]]/Ji Gail becomes King of the [[Zhou dynasty|Zhou Dynasty]] of [[China]].
== Births == * [[Lucius Quinctius Cincinnatus|Cincinnatus]], [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] aristocrat and statesman (d. [[430 BC]]) * [[Xerxes I|Xerxes I of Persia]], fourth [[List of kings of Persia|king]] of [[Achaemenid Empire|Persia]] (or [[518 BC]]) (d. [[465 BC]])
== Deaths ==
* [[Sak of Gojoseon (26th)|King Sak]], 26th king of [[Gija Joseon]]
