[[File:Tunisie_Festival_international_Hammamet.jpg|thumb| Hammamet International Festival]] The ''' Hammamet International Festival''' ({{lang-fr|Festival international d'Hammamet}}) ({{lang-ar|مهرجان الحمامات الدولي}}) is an annual festival of music and art in the coastal city of [[Hammamet, Tunisia|Hammamet]] in Tunisia. It was established in 1964 and is held in July and August in the amphitheatre<ref name="WheelerClammer2010">{{cite book|last1=Wheeler|first1=Donna|last2=Clammer|first2=Paul|last3=Filou|first3=Emilie|title=Tunisia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7RO1b2LvcisC&pg=PA284|year=2010|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-74179-001-6|page=284}}</ref> of 1000 seats overlooking the [[Gulf of Hammamet]]. It is organized by the [[Ministry of Culture (Tunisia)|Ministry of Culture]] , which manages and appoints the director. Since 2014, the Centre and the festival have been under the direction of Kamel Ferjani.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mosaiquefm.net/fr/index/a/ActuDetail/Element/38924-kamel-ferjani-gloria-gaynor-et-cheb-mami-programmes-exclusivement-au-festival-d-hammamet|title=Kamel Ferjani: Gloria Gaynor et Cheb Mami programmés exclusivement au festival d'Hammamet|publisher=Mosaiquefm.net|accessdate=5 June 2015|language=French}}</ref> In the 1980s, [[Ute Lemper]], [[Mikis Theodorakis]], [[Miriam Makeba]] made appearances, and more recently, [[Victoria Abril]], [[Emir Kusturica]], [[Tina Arena]], [[Anouar Brahem]], [[Raouf Ben Yaghlane]], [[Leila Hjaiej]] and French rap group [[IAM4]] have appeared.
