{{Refimprove|date=March 2012}} {{infobox music festival | | music_festival_name = Hideout Festival | image = Hideout Festival, Zrće Beach.jpg | location = [[Zrce]], [[Pag (island)|Pag island]], [[Croatia]] | years_active= 2011 - Present | dates = June — July | genre = [[Electronic dance music|Electronic dance]] | website = http://www.hideoutfestival.com/}}
'''Hideout Festival''' is an annual [[Electronic dance|electronic]] music festival held in [[Zrce]], [[Croatia]] on the island of [[Pag (island)|Pag]]. The first festival was in 2011, and landed on [[The Guardian]]'s list of the best European festivals of 2011,<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/music/2011/may/21/european-festival-listings The best European festivals 2011]</ref> and since then, has sold out every year to date.<ref>[http://www.allaccess.com/net-news/archive/story/154600/croatia-s-hideout-festival-sells-out-for-sixth-yea]</ref> The event is split between pool parties in the day and headline performances at night, both of which take place in Zrce's open-air venues along the beach. There's also a number of boat parties that sail from [[Novalja]] port out onto the Adriatic In 2016, Hideout Festival took place from Sunday 26 June until Thursday 30 June. It was the first year that BBC Radio 1<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.eventmagazine.co.uk/bbc-radio-1-partners-croatias-hideout-festival/brands/article/1388380|title=BBC Radio 1 partners with Croatia's Hideout Festival|website=www.eventmagazine.co.uk|access-date=2016-05-26}}</ref> teamed up with the event for a 3-hour broadcast from a live pool party event hosted by Heidi, Monki and B Traits.In 2017 Hideout festival will take place from Monday 26th – Friday 30 June '''2017'''. 5 days and nights, with over 150 artists including [[Marc Kinchen|MK]] and [[Hannah Wants]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hideoutfestival.com|title=Hideout Festival 2017 • Zrce Beach, Croatia|website=Hideout Festival 2017|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-12-02}}</ref>
Previous guests have included [[Seth Troxler]], [[Nina Kraviz]], [[SBTRKT]], [[Ricardo Villalobos]], [[Annie Mac]], [[Skrillex]], [[Four Tet]], [[Andy C]], [[Jamie Jones (DJ)|Jamie Jones]], [[DJ EZ]], [[Pendulum (drum and bass band)|Pendulum]], [[Modeselektor]], [[Disclosure (band)|Disclosure]], [[Rudimental]], [[Solumun]], [[Sasha (Welsh DJ)|Sasha]], [[Derrick Carter]], [[Gorgon City]], [[Eats Everything]], [[Jamie XX]], [[Hot Since 82]] and [[Hannah Wants]]. For the 2016 edition, Hideout expanded to include Grime artists on the bill, such as [[Skepta]], [[Preditah]] and [[Stormzy]].
The lineup for the 2018 festival includes equally impressive acts, including MK, Patrick Topping, Kerri Chandler, Camelphat, Alan Fitzpatrick to name a few. Standard tickets cost £149 along with a booking fee. The 2018 festival will take place from the 25th of June until the 30th of June. ==See also== {{Commons category|Hideout Festival}} *[[List of electronic music festivals]]
==References== {{reflist}} https://www.hideoutfestival.com/lineup/ ==External links== *{{Official website|http://www.hideoutfestival.com/}}
