==Events== * [[411 BC]] &ndash; The [[Athenian coup of 411 BC|Athenian coup]] succeeds, forming a short-lived [[oligarchy]]. * [[AD 53]] &ndash; The [[Roman emperor]] [[Nero]] marries [[Claudia Octavia]]. * [[AD 68]] &ndash; [[Nero]] commits suicide, after quoting [[Homer]]'s ''[[Iliad]]'', thus ending the [[Julio-Claudian dynasty]] and starting the civil war known as the [[Year of the Four Emperors]]. * [[721]] &ndash; [[Odo of Aquitaine]] defeats the [[Moors]] in the [[Battle of Toulouse (721)|Battle of Toulouse]]. * [[747]] &ndash; [[Abbasid Revolution#Khorosan phase|Abbasid Revolution]]: [[Abu Muslim Khorasani]] begins an open revolt against [[Umayyad Caliphate|Umayyad]] rule, which is carried out under the sign of the [[Black Standard]]. *[[1311]] &ndash; [[Duccio]]'s [[Maestà (Duccio)|Maestà]], a seminal artwork of the early [[Italian Renaissance]], is unveiled and installed in [[Siena Cathedral]] in [[Siena]], Italy. *[[1523]] &ndash; The Parisian Faculty of Theology fines [[Simon de Colines]] for publishing the Biblical commentary ''Commentarii initiatorii in quatuor Evangelia'' by [[Jacques Lefèvre d'Étaples]]. *[[1534]] &ndash; [[Jacques Cartier]] is the first European to describe and map the [[Saint Lawrence River]]. *[[1667]] &ndash; [[Second Anglo-Dutch War]]: The [[Raid on the Medway]] by the Dutch fleet begins. It lasts for five days and results in the worst ever defeat of the [[Royal Navy]]. *[[1732]] &ndash; [[James Oglethorpe]] is granted a [[royal charter]] for the colony of the future U.S. state of [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]]. *[[1762]] &ndash; [[Kingdom of Great Britain|British]] forces begin the [[Battle of Havana (1762)|Siege of Havana]] and capture the city during the [[Seven Years' War]]. *[[1772]] &ndash; The [[Kingdom of Great Britain|British]] [[schooner]] ''[[Gaspee Affair|Gaspee]]'' is burned in Narragansett Bay, [[Rhode Island]]. *[[1798]] &ndash; [[Irish Rebellion of 1798]]: [[Battle of Arklow|Battles of Arklow]] and [[Battle of Saintfield|Saintfield]]. *[[1815]] &ndash; End of the [[Congress of Vienna]]: The new European political situation is set. * 1815 &ndash; [[Luxembourg]] declares independence from the [[First French Empire|French Empire]]. *[[1856]] &ndash; Five hundred [[Mormon handcart pioneers|Mormon]]s leave [[Iowa City, Iowa]] for the [[Mormon Trail]]. *[[1862]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Stonewall Jackson]] concludes his successful [[Jackson's Valley Campaign|Shenandoah Valley Campaign]] with a victory in the [[Battle of Port Republic]]; his tactics during the campaign are now studied by militaries around the world. *[[1863]] &ndash; American Civil War: [[Battle of Brandy Station]], [[Virginia]]. *[[1885]] &ndash; [[Treaty of Tientsin (1885)|Treaty of Tientsin]] is signed to end the [[Sino-French War]], with [[Qing dynasty|China]] eventually giving up [[Tonkin]] and [[Annam (Chinese province)|Annam]] – most of present-day [[Vietnam]] – to France. *[[1900]] &ndash; Indian nationalist [[Birsa Munda]] dies in a British prison of [[cholera]] *[[1915]] &ndash; [[William Jennings Bryan]] resigns as [[Woodrow Wilson]]'s [[United States Secretary of State|Secretary of State]] over a disagreement regarding the United States' handling of the sinking of the {{RMS|Lusitania}}. *[[1923]] &ndash; [[Bulgaria]]'s military takes over the government in a [[Bulgarian coup d'état of 1923|coup]]. *[[1928]] &ndash; [[Charles Kingsford Smith]] completes the first trans-Pacific flight in a [[Fokker F.VII|Fokker Trimotor monoplane]], the ''[[Southern Cross (aircraft)|Southern Cross]]''. *[[1930]] &ndash; A ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' reporter, [[Jake Lingle]], is killed during rush hour at the [[Illinois]] Central train station by [[Leo Vincent Brothers]], allegedly over a $100,000 gambling debt owed to [[Al Capone]]. *[[1934]] &ndash; [[Donald Duck]] makes his debut in ''[[The Wise Little Hen]]''. *[[1944]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: Ninety-nine civilians are [[Tulle massacre|hanged from lampposts and balconies]] by German troops in [[Tulle]], France, in reprisal for [[Maquis du Limousin|maquisards]] attacks. * 1944 &ndash; World War II: The [[Soviet Union]] invades [[East Karelia]] and the [[Karelia (historical province of Finland)|previously Finnish part of Karelia]], occupied by Finland since [[1941]]. *[[1948]] &ndash; Foundation of the [[International Council on Archives]] under the auspices of the UNESCO. *[[1953]] &ndash; The [[Flint–Worcester tornado outbreak sequence]] kills 94 people in [[Massachusetts]]. *[[1954]] &ndash; [[McCarthyism]]: [[Joseph Welch]], special counsel for the United States Army, lashes out at [[United States Senate|Senator]] [[Joseph McCarthy]] during hearings on whether [[Communism]] has infiltrated the Army giving McCarthy the famous rebuke, "You've done enough. Have you no sense of decency, sir, at long last? Have you left no sense of decency?" *[[1957]] &ndash; First ascent of [[Broad Peak]] by [[Fritz Wintersteller]], [[Marcus Schmuck]], [[Kurt Diemberger]], and [[Hermann Buhl]]. *[[1959]] &ndash; The {{USS|George Washington|SSBN-598|6}} is launched. It is the first [[Nuclear power|nuclear-powered]] [[ballistic missile submarine]]. *[[1965]] &ndash; The civilian Prime Minister of [[South Vietnam]], [[Phan Huy Quát]], resigns after being unable to work with a junta led by [[Nguyễn Cao Kỳ]]. * 1965 &ndash; [[Vietnam War]]: The [[Viet Cong]] commences combat with the [[Army of the Republic of Vietnam]] in the [[Battle of Dong Xoai|Battle of Đồng Xoài]], one of the largest battles in the war. *[[1967]] &ndash; [[Six-Day War]]: [[Israel]] captures the [[Golan Heights]] from [[Syria]]. *[[1968]] &ndash; U.S. President [[Lyndon B. Johnson]] declares a national day of mourning following the [[assassination of Senator Robert F. Kennedy]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; Severe rainfall causes a dam in the [[Black Hills]] of [[South Dakota]] to burst, creating [[1972 Black Hills flood|a flood]] that kills 238 people and causes $160 million in damage. *[[1973]] &ndash; In horse racing, [[Secretariat (horse)|Secretariat]] wins the [[Triple Crown of Thoroughbred Racing|U.S. Triple Crown]]. *[[1978]] &ndash; [[The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints]] opens its [[Priesthood (Latter Day Saints)|priesthood]] to "all worthy men", ending a 148-year-old policy of excluding black men. *[[1979]] &ndash; The [[1979 Sydney Ghost Train fire|Ghost Train fire]] at [[Luna Park Sydney]], Australia, kills seven. *[[1999]] &ndash; [[Kosovo War]]: The [[Federal Republic of Yugoslavia]] and [[NATO]] sign a [[peace treaty]]. *[[2008]] &ndash; [[2008 Beni Amrane bombings|Two bombs explode]] at a train station near [[Algiers|Algiers, Algeria]], killing at least 13 people. *[[2009]] &ndash; An [[Pearl Continental hotel bombing|explosion]] kills 17 people and injures at least 46 at a hotel in [[Peshawar]], [[Pakistan]]. *[[2010]] &ndash; At least 40 people are killed and more than 70 wounded in a [[Nadahan wedding bombing|suicide bombing]] at a wedding party in [[Arghandab District|Arghandab]], [[Kandahar]].
