yes]], French geologist and conchologist (b. 1795) *[[1889]] &ndash; [[Mike Burke (shortstop)|Mike Burke]], American baseball player (b. 1854) *[[1892]] &ndash; [[William Grant Stairs]], Canadian-English captain and explorer (b. 1863) *[[1901]] &ndash; [[Adolf Bötticher]], German historian and author (b. 1842) *[[1923]] &ndash; [[Princess Helena of the United Kingdom]] (b. 1846) *[[1927]] &ndash; [[Victoria Woodhull]], American activist for women's rights (b. 1838) *[[1929]] &ndash; [[Louis Bennison]], American stage and silent film actor (b. 1884) * 1929 &ndash; [[Margaret Lawrence (actress)|Margaret Lawrence]], American stage actress (b. 1889) *[[1942]] &ndash; [[František Erben]], Czech gymnast (b. 1874) *[[1952]] &ndash; [[Adolf Busch]], German-Austrian violinist and composer (b. 1891) *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Ernest Graves, Sr.]], American football player, coach, and general (b. 1880) *1956 &ndash; [[Chandrashekhar Agashe]], Indian industrialist and lawyer (b. 1888) *1956 &ndash; [[Hans Bergsland]], Norwegian fencer (b. 1878) *1956 &ndash; [[Thomas Hicks (tennis)|Thomas Hicks]], Australian tennis player (b. 1869) *1956 &ndash; [[Ferdinand Jodl]], German general (b. 1896) *[[1958]] &ndash; [[Robert Donat]], English actor (b. 1905) *[[1959]] &ndash; [[Adolf Otto Reinhold Windaus]], German chemist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1876) *[[1960]] &ndash; [[Harry S. Hammond]], American football player and businessman (b. 1884) *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Camille Guérin]], French veterinarian, bacteriologist and immunologist (b. 1872) *[[1963]] &ndash; [[Jacques Villon]], French painter (b.1875) *[[1964]] &ndash; [[Max Aitken, 1st Baron Beaverbrook]], British businessman and politician, [[Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster]] (b. 1879) *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Bernard Cronin]], Australian author and journalist (b. 1884) *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Gilberto Parlotti]], Italian motorcycle racer (b. 1940) *[[1973]] &ndash; [[Chuck Bennett]], American football 