{{Infobox convention |name = MINExpo International |image = Model in Hydraulic Shovel at MinExpo 2008.JPG |alt = a female model, in a red top and black skirt, standing (with her hands on her hips) in a (bright yellow) bucket of an hydraulic shovel in the exhibit hall of MINExpo 2008. The model is standing behind a velvet rope discouraging trade show attendees from standing in the bucket. Another exhibit is visible in the background as is a group of approximately 12 attendees all but one of which appear to me men. |caption = A model in the bucket of a hydraulic shovel at MINExpo International 2008 |status = |genre = |venue = [[Las Vegas Convention Center]] |location = [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]] |coordinates = |country = |first = |last = {{End date|2016|9|30}} |attendance = |organizer = [[National Mining Association]] |filing = |website = {{URL|minexpo.com/}} |footnotes = |frequency = Quadrennially <!-- Weekly, Monthly, Quarterly, Semi-annually, Annually, Bi-annually, 2nd Tuesday of November, etc. --> }}
'''MINExpo International''' is a [[trade show]] sponsored by the [[National Mining Association]].<ref name="EMJ">{{cite journal|date=November 2008|title=MINExpo Brings it All Together|journal=Engineering & Mining Journal|location=United States|volume=209|issue=9|pages=30|issn=0095-8948}}</ref> The show exhibits the latest [[mining]] and [[mineral]]s processing technologies, and state-of-the-art [[machinery]] and equipment for the coal, metal and nonmetal mining processing industries. MINExpo International 2008 is thought to have been the largest mining trade show in the world.<ref name="below">{{cite journal|last=Robison|first=Jennifer|date=Sep 23, 2008|title=For Good News, Go Below Surface|journal=[[Las Vegas Review-Journal]]|location=[[Las Vegas, Nevada]]|url=http://www.lvrj.com/business/29582589.html|accessdate=2009-03-30}}</ref>
MINExpo International is held every four years and has been held at the [[Las Vegas Convention Center]] since 1996.<ref name="skil">{{cite journal|date=November 2008|title=Bigger Trucks, Faster Shovels, and More Miners|journal=Skillins Mining Review|volume=97|issue=11|pages=2}}</ref> The 2008 MINExpo drew over 44,000 people (an increase of over 44% from the previous show in 2004) and 1,025 exhibitors in an area of {{convert|600000|ft2}}<ref name="EMJ"/><ref name="below"/><ref name="skil"/>
