{{Politics of Nagorno-Karabakh}}
An '''[[independence referendum]]''' was held in [[Nagorno-Karabakh Republic|Nagorno-Karabakh]] on 10 December 1991.<ref name=DD>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=az031991 Berg-Karabach (Aserbeidschan), 10. Dezember 1991 : Unabhängigkeit] Direct Democracy</ref> It was approved by 99.98% of voters.<ref name=DD/> It was unsuccessfully boycotted by the region's [[Azerbaijani people|Azeri]] population, which then constituted 20% of its population. The referendum was held without consent of the [[Azerbaijan|Republic of Azerbaijan]], and is not recognized internationally by the [[Member states of the United Nations|UN member states]].
==Results== {| class=wikitable style=text-align:right !Choice !Votes !% |- |align=left|For||108,615||99.98 |- |align=left|Against||24||0.02 |- |align=left|Invalid/blank votes||95||– |- |align=left|'''Total'''||'''108,736'''||'''100''' |- |align=left|Registered voters/turnout||132,328||82.17 |- |colspan=3 align=left|Source: [http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=az031991 Direct Democracy] |}
